            <article data-uuid="53b87b9efa06450280dd8cb9e2412e19">
                <h3 class="eq" data-uuid="52b3f81ccf8640ebbdedd0eca42561e8">Essential Question</h3>
                <h3 class="eqt" data-uuid="40d0798aa7de43c485fd0c35180fb622">Which ideas in the
                    Constitution are most important for preserving freedom?</h3>
                <p data-uuid="aa18898e69d2480395a68b8ec6a541d1">The U.S. Constitution is the world’s oldest
                    written constitution still in effect. The framers of the Constitution are
                    widely praised for creating a government that represents the interests of the
                    majority while protecting individual rights. They also included a process for
                    amending, or revising, the Constitution as the nation changes over time.
                    Although the framers lived in a world very different from our own, their words
                    continue to guide us. Which ideas in the Constitution do you think are most
                    important for preserving freedom?&#160;</p>
                <p data-uuid="a00d17bbec9b425baa28612fb43e3a1a">As you read this module, consider why
                    particular ideas were written into the Constitution and how they affect our lives.
                    When you are done, you will write a short essay answering the Essential
                    Question for this module.</p>
            </article>
            <section class="video-container " data-uuid="a6213633b3c24bb9b4ae872121672752">
                <article data-uuid="65fe410f49484818ae970bd091ab5a1b">
                    <h3 class="vid" data-uuid="cd91bfd3494941a7888775557665423b">Could You Pass the U.S. Citizenship Test?<br />
                    </h3>
                    <p class="vid" data-uuid="9abebbfab2a245c89bd9aa385f486102">Immigrants to the United States must study the Constitution and U.S. history in order to pass a citizenship test. Yet many Americans who were born in this country or have lived here for decades would find such a test difficult to pass.<br />
                    </p>
